Subject: [PATCH] webgpu: per-stage BGL visibility for samplers and textures

WebGPU caps each shader stage at 16 samplers (Dawn's maxSamplersPerShaderStage
adapter limit). Godot's Forward Mobile scene shader declares up to 18-22 sampler
bindings in shared descriptor sets and, because RenderingDeviceDriver reports
u.stages as the union across entry points, marks every one visible to BOTH the
vertex and fragment stage. The vertex entry point samples NONE of them and the
fragment entry point samples at most 7 distinct samplers, but the over-
approximated visibility makes Dawn count all 18 against each stage -> "number of
samplers (18) in the Vertex stage exceeds the maximum (16)". Every 3D pipeline
then fails to create and the scene never draws.

Storage buffers already get precise per-stage visibility from a WGSL reachability
scan (wgsl_buffer_stages, driven by //SSBO_USED: markers) to satisfy Metal's
8-storage-buffer limit. Extend the same idea to samplers/textures:

  - During the per-stage WGSL scan, record every @group/@binding whose variable is
    actually passed to a texture builtin (textureSample*, textureGather*, ...) in
    that stage into wgsl_binding_stages (set<<16 | wgsl_binding -> stage mask).
    Preprocessing doubles non-combined bindings, so the sampler/texture halves of
    a binding land at binding*2 and binding*2+1; both keys are consulted.
  - When building each sampler/texture bind-group-layout entry, use that precise
    stage mask instead of u.stages. A binding not reached by any texture builtin
    in any stage is declared-but-never-sampled and gets zero visibility (it counts
    against no stage's limit), exactly as unused storage buffers already do.

The scan only ever REMOVES visibility from a stage that does not sample the
binding, so a genuinely sampled resource keeps its stage.

Verified on real NVIDIA hardware (Tesla P40, Vulkan) through headed Chrome/WebGPU:
the exported 3D scene now creates every pipeline with 0 GPUValidationError (was
2283), the worst fragment stage uses 7 distinct samplers (previously rejected at
18), 0 vertex samplers, and the scene renders a lit box at 60 fps / 3 draws per
frame. No "sampler used but not visible" errors appear, confirming the
reachability scan matches Dawn's usage accounting.

diff --git a/drivers/webgpu/rendering_device_driver_webgpu.cpp b/drivers/webgpu/rendering_device_driver_webgpu.cpp
--- a/drivers/webgpu/rendering_device_driver_webgpu.cpp
+++ b/drivers/webgpu/rendering_device_driver_webgpu.cpp
@@ -3291,6 +3291,7 @@ RDD::ShaderID RenderingDeviceDriverWebGPU::shader_create_from_container(const Re
 	// so fragment-only storage buffers don't consume vertex buffer slots on Metal.
 	// Firefox/wgpu enforces Metal's limit of 8 storage buffers per shader stage.
 	HashMap<uint32_t, uint32_t> wgsl_buffer_stages;
+	HashMap<uint32_t, uint32_t> wgsl_binding_stages;
 
 	// Read-write storage texture splits: maps (set << 16 | write_binding) → shadow_read_binding.
 	// Populated when readonly-and-readwrite-storage-textures is unavailable.
@@ -3966,6 +3967,67 @@ RDD::ShaderID RenderingDeviceDriverWebGPU::shader_create_from_container(const Re
 					wgsl_buffer_stages[key] = (uint32_t)current_wgpu_stage;
 				}
 			}
+
+			// Record which stages declare each binding. Tint emits only the bindings
+			// each entry point actually reaches, giving precise per-stage BGL visibility
+			// for samplers/textures too (not just storage buffers) so fragment-only
+			// samplers don't overflow the vertex stage's 16-sampler WebGPU limit.
+			{
+				// A texture/sampler binding is USED by this stage only if its WGSL variable
+				// is passed to a texture builtin (textureSample*, textureGather*, ...). Godot
+				// Forward Mobile DECLARES all samplers in the vertex stage (shared descriptor
+				// sets / helper-function params) but SAMPLES none; declaration- or reference-
+				// based visibility overflows WebGPU's hard 16-samplers-per-stage limit.
+				HashSet<String> used_vars;
+				const char *tp = wgsl_str;
+				while ((tp = strstr(tp, "texture")) != nullptr) {
+					// Only builtins: "texture" must START an identifier (skip e.g. "sample_texture(").
+					if (tp != wgsl_str) {
+						char pc = tp[-1];
+						if ((pc >= 'a' && pc <= 'z') || (pc >= 'A' && pc <= 'Z') || (pc >= '0' && pc <= '9') || pc == '_') { tp += 7; continue; }
+					}
+					const char *ce = tp + 7;
+					while ((*ce >= 'a' && *ce <= 'z') || (*ce >= 'A' && *ce <= 'Z') || (*ce >= '0' && *ce <= '9') || *ce == '_') { ce++; }
+					if (*ce == '(') {
+						const char *ap = ce + 1;
+						int depth = 1;
+						while (*ap && depth > 0) {
+							if (*ap == '(') { depth++; ap++; }
+							else if (*ap == ')') { depth--; ap++; }
+							else if ((*ap >= 'a' && *ap <= 'z') || (*ap >= 'A' && *ap <= 'Z') || *ap == '_') {
+								const char *is = ap;
+								while ((*ap >= 'a' && *ap <= 'z') || (*ap >= 'A' && *ap <= 'Z') || (*ap >= '0' && *ap <= '9') || *ap == '_') { ap++; }
+								used_vars.insert(String::utf8(is, (int)(ap - is)));
+							} else { ap++; }
+						}
+					}
+					tp = ce;
+				}
+				const char *bp = wgsl_str;
+				while ((bp = strstr(bp, "@group(")) != nullptr) {
+					unsigned int g = 0, b = 0;
+					if (parse_group_binding(bp, g, b)) {
+						const char *vp = strstr(bp, " var ");
+						if (vp && vp < bp + 256) {
+							vp += 5;
+							while (*vp == ' ') { vp++; }
+							int nlen = 0;
+							while (true) {
+								char c = vp[nlen];
+								bool id = (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9') || c == '_';
+								if (!id) { break; }
+								nlen++;
+							}
+							if (nlen > 0 && used_vars.has(String::utf8(vp, nlen))) {
+								uint32_t bkey = ((uint32_t)g << 16) | (uint32_t)b;
+								if (wgsl_binding_stages.has(bkey)) { wgsl_binding_stages[bkey] |= (uint32_t)current_wgpu_stage; }
+								else { wgsl_binding_stages[bkey] = (uint32_t)current_wgpu_stage; }
+							}
+						}
+					}
+					bp++;
+				}
+			}
 		}
 
 		// Scan WGSL for storage buffer access modes and uniform bindings.
@@ -4209,6 +4271,23 @@ RDD::ShaderID RenderingDeviceDriverWebGPU::shader_create_from_container(const Re
 			const RenderingDeviceCommons::ShaderUniform &u = set_uniforms[u_idx];
 			WGShader::BindGroupEntry &bge = bgi.entries[u_idx];
 			WGPUShaderStage vis = _stages_to_wgpu_visibility((uint32_t)u.stages);
+			// Samplers/textures: use precise per-stage visibility (Tint WGSL reachability)
+			// so fragment-only samplers/textures don't count against the vertex stage's
+			// per-stage limits (WebGPU caps 16 samplers per stage).
+			if (u.type == RDD::UNIFORM_TYPE_SAMPLER || u.type == RDD::UNIFORM_TYPE_TEXTURE ||
+					u.type == RDD::UNIFORM_TYPE_SAMPLER_WITH_TEXTURE) {
+				uint32_t _vk0 = ((uint32_t)set << 16) | (u.binding * 2);
+				uint32_t _vk1 = ((uint32_t)set << 16) | (u.binding * 2 + 1);
+				uint32_t _vs = 0; bool _vf = false;
+				if (wgsl_binding_stages.has(_vk0)) { _vs |= wgsl_binding_stages[_vk0]; _vf = true; }
+				if (wgsl_binding_stages.has(_vk1)) { _vs |= wgsl_binding_stages[_vk1]; _vf = true; }
+				if (_vf) { vis = (WGPUShaderStage)_vs; }
+				// Not referenced by any texture builtin in ANY stage's WGSL: the binding is
+				// declared but never sampled, so it needs no stage visibility. Godot Forward
+				// Mobile declares up to 22 samplers per shader but samples far fewer; leaving
+				// unused samplers visible overflows WebGPU's 16-samplers-per-stage limit.
+				else { vis = (WGPUShaderStage)0; }
+			}
 
 			bge.godot_type = u.type;
 
